Consider theoretical and practical approaches to aquisition of mother tongue, foreign language and Estonian language by both children and adults.Objectives/eesmärkid:  inroduce to language development of children, ways and methods of second language aquisition by adults.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) has an overview of the main notions and issues of (second) language acquisition, theoretical schools, development trends, and topical problems; 2) has essential knowledge about (second) language acquisition and bilingualism and are able to apply the acquired knowledge in their professional activities; 3) has a critical understanding of the problems of (second) language acquisition, can analyse them and evaluate different solutions; 4) knows the most important theories and is thoroughly familiar with the main reserach trends of (second) language acquisition.
